                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2004-01-09</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>Whether you're a Christian looking for inspiration in your faith or a non-Christian after an amazing insight into the spiritual side of the church, this book won't disappoint! It is generally a pretty easy read with short chapters on defined topics. As such, the translation seems quite good. Thomas a Kempis soaks the pages with the love and peace that he has acquired from hir religion. The book contains many moral and ethical lessons on peace and humility that as needed in our world as ever. And this is done in a tone that is far from the dry dogmatic style of many other Christian fathers.<p>It's easy to see why, outside the Bible, this has been one of the most popular Christian books!</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">a must have</div>
